Author: Nikolas.Glushe
Title: [ANN] Dentacoin [DCN] - The Blockchain Solution For The Global Dental Industry
Body: Dear Dentacoin community. We, a team of enthusiasts, are pleased to inform you about our project https://dchats.info/ which logs all the important telegram chats related to Dentacoin. We believe that Dentacoin Chats will be a valuable addition to the Dentacoin ecosystem. During the work of the site, we have already received a large number of positive feedback from community members. The project is under active development. The project has its own team of programmers, ready at any time to solve new technical problems and make new improvements.  What is implemented at the moment: You can read your favorite chats in the form convenient for you through https://dchats.info/ The site is optimized for work also on mobile devices. There is a search by keyword and date. It is possible to read the chat you want in your native language using Google Translate. The translation is not perfect, but it will allow you to receive the latest news as quickly as possible from the first sources. For example, you can use our site to read Spanish, English, Korean and other versions of Dentacoin telegram chat.  In the near future, we plan to add the ability to share a specific telegram post in social networks. On the one hand, it will allow you to share interesting content with your friends and subscribers, and on the other hand, it will positively influence the development of Dentacoin’s popularity in general.  There is a lot of work ahead, we have planned a huge number of interesting and useful improvements. If you have any suggestions for improving our site, please write - we will try to take everything into account and use it in the further development of the site.  If you think that some important chat related to Dentacoin is missing on our site, please write and we will add it.

Author: jerry3k5jamiso1
Title: [ANN] Dentacoin [DCN] - The Blockchain Solution For The Global Dental Industry
Body: Dentacoin Enhances its Identity Verification Process as it Partners Up With Civic  Dentacoin, a well-renowned blockchain-based project aimed at uniting the dental community from across the globe, has partnered up with Civic to enhance its identity verification process. Dentacoin has integrated support for CivicConnect, which is an app-to-app integration product launched by Civic. CivicConnect allows different apps to perform identity verifications procedures which make sure that the accounts used are of actual real-life people. Civic identity verification procedure will now be integrated into all the Dentacoin tools from DentaVox to Dentacare Health Training App.  https://blockpublisher.com/dentacoin-enhances-its-identity-verification-process-as-it-partners-up-with-civic/  [/i]

Now, let's apply the scenario to a worse situation where at least there is a nine tenth of clinic that didn't use DCN, your number will significantly decreasing.  Let's talk about thw truth that there is a very possible event where someone doesn't need a dental visit his entire life, or let's talk about a chance where the not-wealthy people can't afford a dental clinic, let alone buying crypto. Author: group3
Title: [ANN] Dentacoin [DCN] - The Blockchain Solution For The Global Dental Industry
Body: Judging from comments on multiple social media platforms and cryptocurrency enthusiasts, it is clear to see that there seems to be a consensus to have the supply of this coin reduced. I only wish that the development and management team would see the economics of giving this some serious thought. I do understand the argument of having the tokens locked in and released on a predetermined schedule and the justification of having enough coin supply for a global market, but the economics just does not make sense when it boils down to the competition faced by the vast majority of coins out there on the market, some with very similar objectives and use cases and with drastically lower supply.  Etherium current supply= 98, 000, 000 Ripple= 39 B,   and total supply 100B  As for medical tokens;  Medibloc total supply= 4B Medicalchain total supply= 500 mln  Dentacoin current supply= 325 B and Total supply is 8 trillion  Now how can you possibly compete sustainably with such high supply???  Another argument that I've heard is juxtaposing the supply to the total number of circulating USD fiat currency thereby justifying the need to allow for enough circulating supply. I simply don't buy that argument because simply, crypto currency in generally is seen as deflationary by nature and can't be seen in the same  light as fiat currency. Not to completely forget utility tokens, but even they are also used as store of value based on a very speculative crypto market. if we are to see crypto tokens as having some form of store of value definition, then the economics would make sense to reduce the price. As a holder of this coin, I honestly believe in the vision and the team, but I would again urge the reduction in the supply to at least less than 100 billion to allow for sustained growth and attract more investors (what have we to lose, but a lot to gain)

Author: crevbi
Title: [ANN] Dentacoin [DCN] - The Blockchain Solution For The Global Dental Industry
Body: Dentacoin Announces Strategic Partnership with Arklign, San Jose, CA February 7th, 2018: Dentacoin made a significant breakthrough towards its wider acceptance within the industry as it started partnering with Arklign, a state-of-the-art full service dental laboratory partner, based in San Jose, California!  Arklign: Transforming the Dental Lab Experience Arklign is an innovative company, uniquely positioned as an end-to-end partner for dental service providers. It uconnects and transforms the dental lab experience by centralizing workflow and automating communication while simultaneously providing a personalized, hands-on approach to customer service.  Arklign’s offering consists of the dental restorations fabricated by its lab and Arklign Case Relationship Management (aCRM), a proprietary online platform through which customers track and manage the restoration cases handled by Arklign. Arklign’s full-service dental lab offers a comprehensive range of solutions for fixed restorations, removable restorations and implant restorations, and benefits from a distributed global operations model that is driven by technology and automation, allowing for 24-hour operations and maximized efficiency in creating high quality dental restorations in a timely manner.  With Arklign, dental practices benefit from a systemized workflow, data insights and high-volume laboratory capabilities that make their business more efficient.  The idea to provide value-based and affordable services within the dental industry through a highly efficient approach naturally led Ray Alde, CEO of Arklign, to Dentacoin. Now Dentacoin is implemented into Arklign’s payment options, allowing dentists to pay a percentage of their bills in the industry-specific currency! In the future, Dentacoin could also be utilized in Arklign’s own rewards program via their Case Relationship Management platform (aCRM), which will be another big step forward! https://blog.dentacoin.com/dentacoin-announces-strategic-partnership-arklign-san-jose-ca/

Author: gartmah
Title: [ANN] Dentacoin [DCN] - The Blockchain Solution For The Global Dental Industry
Body: 3 TOKENS TO WATCH IN 2018   Beyond Bitcoin, Ethereum, and Ripple, the “crypto world” is comprised of a multitude of tokens supporting diverse blockchain projects. There is literally something for everyone. Here are three tokens that caught my attention in recent times.    DENTACOIN (DCN) Market Cap as of 01/15/2018 ($912,298,386 USD)  https://dentacoin.com/  Dentacoin is a blockchain concept aiming to improve the dental care industry. The associated Dentacoin ERC20 token was conceived to be used globally by all individuals.  The Dentacoin team launched its first tools last year:  Trusted Review Platform: this framework rewards patients for posting unedited reviews of the care they have received onto a blockchain.   Dentavox: a customer intelligence platform which seeks users’ opinions on dental health topics.  Dentacare: a mobile app that rewards people for establishing healthy dental care habits.   VIBE (VIBE) Market Cap as of 01/15/2018 ($224,683,933 USD)  https://www.vibehub.io/  VIBEHub is aiming to become a substantial VR and AR marketplace and hub. VibeHub’s initial token offering (ITO) recently made a lot of noise, becoming sold out in less than 5 minutes, raising $10 million (USD) in the process. Furthermore, the value of its token “Vibe” increased by a staggering 400% on January 10 (which put the price per coin above Ripple).  The project’s FAQ provides some insights on what users can expect in the future:  “You will be able to attend concerts, education seminars, play games and go on virtual dates all in VR on the VIBEHub application. VIBEHub will also focus on AR (Augmented Reality) as well, and will be available as those device become mainstream. You will also be able to access the platform without a VR or AR device, in a less immersive experience through modern browsers, Allowing everyone to participate.”  CYBERMILES (CMT) Market Cap as of 01/15/2018 ($167,413,783 USD)  https://cm.5miles.com/  CyberMiles is a new blockchain platform designed for commercial applications. CyberMiles has announced its first strategic partnership with peer-to-peer marketplace, 5miles. The platform aims to empower the decentralization of online marketplaces, it recently concluded an initial coin offering, raising close to $30 million (USD) from more than 100 countries.  2018 is a promising year for crypto tokens and I’m looking forward to learn about new exciting blockchain-related projects.  The information provided on this article does not constitute investment advice, financial advice, trading advice or any other sort of advice.  http://www.hashtaginvesting.com/blog/2018/1/15/3-tokens-to-watch-in-2018

Title: [ANN] Dentacoin [DCN] - The Blockchain Solution For The Global Dental Industry
Body: With a trillion coins supply, it'll be a cold day in hell before this coin could EVER ... EVER reach $1 in our life time. They need to burn some of it and do a coin swap like PACC is planning on doing if this coin is to gain any meaningful value.  Second, on the business feasibility side - the whitepaper is nothing but one person's wishful thinking and daydreaming. Why exactly would anyone want to first convert fiat to a digital currency which could ONLY be used at a dentist' office? And, just how often do we go to see dentist .... perhaps 3-5 times a year on average. What benefits dentists are missing in fiat that they'll find in DCN? And more importantly, in most first world countries, healthcare is heavily dominated by insurance companies. How is DCN going to remove this middleman and connect patients directly to dentist?  Like most other coins, it uses future tense for all its claims and heavy on outlandish prophecies but rather empty on specifics. It is just good for holding for some time, make some good money and move on to bigger things.

Author: keystoneminer
Title: [ANN] Dentacoin [DCN] - The Blockchain Solution For The Global Dental Industry
Body: I think this is also a project with potential.  This is a ton of change happening in the good old dental industry.  There is consolidation happening on a large scale.  For example based in Fort Washington, PA there is a company called DentaWeb.  They are an Indian based company of highly successful Dentists that has interesting things going on - most of which involve data centralization. They are cash rich and have purchased well over 600 private dental practices in the Northeast US.  All practices are tied back to Ft Washington via a VPN. They have a centralized English speaking call center in Ft Washington where all patient calls are fielded, appts are made, billing, records etc.  They are also a distributor and enabler of modern dental technology. They have classroom learning where they bring in experts from abroad to tech the very latest and most advanced techniques.  Its an old industry that everyone needs especially the immigrant population.  Overseas having straight teeth is not nearly as important as it is here in the USA therefore tens of thousands of those people will be spending their present and future income on dental. They tend to have big families - again more demand for Dental - an industry that traditionally is funded more out of pocket than plan paid - trust me I know from experience even the very very plans max out quickly if your mouth is having a bad year.  One good crown or root canal wipes out your benefit and the rest is cash out of pocket.  Firms like GE Finance are quick to take advantage offering instant in office credit at 22% - yes I think more and more there is vast potential for such a platform.

Author: Nirmalpandey
Title: [ANN] Dentacoin [DCN] - The Blockchain Solution For The Global Dental Industry
Body: Written by Mariam Nishanian, Online Reputation and Public Relations, Dentacoin Foundation   The crypto-world describes two ways to achieve value in a cryptocurrency. It has suggested that “saver coins” are the best way to achieve lasting savings. The argument is that a rising price, such as Bitcoin has enjoyed, is an important deflationary component to successful long-term savings.  “Spender coins”, on the other hand, are theoretically inflationary and are not good long-term stores of value. The argument is that as the price of everything goes up, a coin that actually buys things will automatically decrease in value. According to “experts” and many recent blog posts, this makes “spender coins” a poor choice as a way to build value over the long-run.  Problem #1 This line of thinking has many mistakes, but the greatest one is a complete misunderstanding of the meaning of value. A currency – crypto or otherwise – only has value because it can be converted into something the holder wants. Dollars can be converted into a house or a car or a meal, so dollars have value.  What individuals who argue that Bitcoin is a “saver coin” forget is that Bitcoin only has value because it can be converted into dollars! While the original intention was to create a way for anonymous transactions, most people own Bitcoin for the potential price appreciation. They have no intention of ever buying anything with their Bitcoin without first converting the cryptocurrency into dollars (or Euros or some other national currency).  It’s true that some retailers are beginning to accept Bitcoin as payment, but the bill that is being paid is still expressed in dollars! Accepting Bitcoin is just a way to make paying in dollars (or Euros or some other national currency) easier. The retailer does the conversion to dollars, and gets a marketing edge over competitors by accepting Bitcoin.  Problem #2 Acceptance and use determine value, not intention. The price of Bitcoin has skyrocketed because more and more people are accepting it as a legitimate investment. It’s that simple. Any coin that grows in acceptance and use will see an increase in value. This happens with national currencies too. A loss of confidence in a national currency causes an increase in the acceptance and use of dollars (or Euros or some other national currency) in that nation.  So a coin like Dentacoin that is growing in acceptance and use in the global dental industry should see an increase in value, even though it is a “spender coin”. It will be deflationary and a long-term “saver coin” even though it is supposed to experience an erosion of value due to inflation in the upcoming years, until 2042, when the planned annual distribution will be completed.  In addition, acceptance and use for a “spender coin” like Dentacoin means getting a dental treatment, dental supplies or a dental review with the cryptocurrency. Acceptance and use for Bitcoin means being able to quickly and easily convert it into dollars. A single incident where multiple investors cannot do this – known in financial circles as a liquidity crisis – would damage Bitcoin’s acceptance and a part of its value.  Problem #3 No one can overcome the laws of supply and demand over the long run. Gold has value in part because it is rare. All the gold that has ever been mined in the history of the world would fill less than 3 1/2 Olympic swimming pools. Bitcoin has profited from a perception that it is scarce, but that perception is a mistake.  First of all, every Bitcoin can be broken down into 100 million Satoshi. This is the real unit of the cryptocurrency. In comparison, the total amount of Dentacoin that will ever be issued is less than the current supply of Bitcoin units (a.k.a. Satoshi) currently on the market. In addition, new Bitcoin is being added to the supply continually.  While much has been said about the “total supply” of Bitcoin as a fixed amount, the reality is that “hard forks” in the Bitcoin blockchain have eliminated this limit.  Although the new cryptocurrencies have names like “Bitcoin Cash” or “Bitcoin Gold”, they have value because of their association with Bitcoin and effectively increase the total supply of the Bitcoin “brand”.  So, What is Value? The acceptance and use of a cryptocurrency gives it real long-term value. This is the next development in the world of blockchain, and it is already taking place. Political arguments regarding de-centralized authority are less important than the real-world goods and services that can be obtained with the coin.  As a cryptocurrency designed for the global dental industry, Dentacoin is tied to the value of the services it buys. An increasing cost of services will increase the value of Dentacoin. Keep in mind that this is only a measure of value, so better services at a lower price – better value – will also be reflected in the market price of Dentacoin.  The Dentacoin Assurance smart contract is another significant value creation opportunity.  The unique approach – which will only be available through the Dentacoin Ecosystem – aligns the financial incentives of both dentists and patients in achieving better dental health. This value should also be reflected in the future market price of Dentacoin.

Author: Nirmalpandey
Title: [ANN] Dentacoin [DCN] - The Blockchain Solution For The Global Dental Industry
Body: English_Translation New cryptocurrency finds its way into modern dentistry  Varna, 14.12.2017 (lifePR) - The public interest in topics related to Bitcoin and Co. currently seems almost inexhaustible. Cryptocurrencies based on Blockchain technology are hotly debated in many industries. One aspect, which is usually the focus here, is the potential increase in value, which in the "Bitcoin boom" has turned into a real - and not insignificant - increase in value.  But the potential of Blockchain goes far beyond mere monetary benefits. Due to its intrinsic properties, it is ideally suited as a basis for various technologies and concepts that are geared to accuracy and transparency. In terms of a "digital database", the blockchain has three main features:  Decentralization : There is no central authority exercising administrative power. The data is in the form of a network structure in copy with all users involved.  Transparency : The decentralization results in a transparency for all users who have corresponding access rights.  Immutability : All data added to the blockchain will remain in its original state. They can not be changed or deleted. This makes the digital database almost completely tamper-proof. The Dentacoin Foundation from the Netherlands has recognized and exploited the opportunities offered by blockchain technology to implement a revolutionary project in the field of dentistry. With the first Ethereum Blockchain-based custom token especially for the dental industry, it has paved the way for a modern and, above all, patient-centered dentistry.  SWISS Dentaprime has integrated this custom token - called dentacoin (DCN) - into its treatment concept as the first dental clinic to focus even more on consistent patient centering .  In the 3-month trial period (March to May 2017), Dentacoin has proven to be the optimal integrative tool for daily workflow.  The key features of the custom token are developed as part of a patient loyalty program, helping to strengthen patient loyalty and optimize quality management. Patients receive Dentacoin credited to their digital wallet for their feedback on each treatment step. These can be credited to the payment amount at their next treatment. Through constant and authentic feedback, the Dentaprime Dental Clinic can make processes that increase service and treatment quality more targeted and thus more effective: a win-win situation. Because the patient benefits not only from a discount on the invoice amount, as is the case with conventional coupons or the like, but also from a treatment based on his feedback or adapted.  The patient reactions in the test phase were consistently positive. Even if it is of course a concept that needs explanation. In constant exchange and with constant support from the Dentacoin Foundation, communication concepts tailored to different audiences have been developed to help all patients understand how the loyalty program works.  Although many patients have used their dentacoin as a means of payment for their treatment, there are some who are so intrigued by the cryptocurrency that they consider it an investment with potential value and even ask for additional ways to obtain DCN. Therefore, the Dentaprime Dental Clinic has extended the loyalty program to various evaluation options and referrals.  In addition, a catalog of selected dental care products is planned that patients can purchase with their DCN.  Since the possibilities for using the custom token are basically unlimited, the Dentaprime dental clinic is very excited about future developments and of course keeps you as a reader up to date.  Health & Medicine  http://www.klamm.de/news/neue-cryptowaehrung-haelt-einzug-in-die-moderne-zahnmedizin-19N687178.html

Author: Artemsv
Title: [ANN] Dentacoin [DCN] - The Blockchain Solution For The Global Dental Industry
Body: First clinic in Taiwan accepts Dentacoin: Mr. iTeeth, Taipei City    We are happy to announce the first partner clinic in Taiwan, accepting Dentacoin as means of payment: Mr. iTeeth, located in Taipei City!  The practice is specialized in prosthodontics, orthodontics, endodontics and implantology and has six dental practitioners. Modern open dental treatment rooms, designed with comfort in mind, maximize patient flow and allow for more efficient visits. The specialists at Mr. iTeeth aim at providing excellent customer service and pay significant attention on educating patients on variety of dental health related topics such as the importance of proper dental hygiene, good nutrition, etc. The staff is highly focused on utilizing new technological advances.  Having realized the potential benefits from implementing Dentacoin, Tung Hao Lin, prosthodontist and implantologist at Mr. iTeeth Dental Clinic, initiated a contact with our team.  From today, December 12, 2017 patients can pay for their dental treatment at the Taiwanese clinic with Dentacoin (DCN). “I read about Dentacoin and I was fascinated by the concept. Back then, the ICO was still running, so I decided to join and support the project. I believe in the future potential of Dentacoin and I hope that some day soon, not only my patients will use DCN as means of payment, but I will also be able to purchase dental materials and equipment”, explains Lin.  Mr. iTeeth is the fourth clinic which not only uses the Dentacoin tools, but also accepts Dentacoin as means of payment. The other partner clinics include: F3T Dental Clinic (London, United Kingdom), Swiss Dentaprime (Varna, Bulgaria), Dentech Dental Care (Pune, India). Simultaneously, the number of dental practices registered on the Trusted Review Platform is increasing day by day and at the moment of writing it is 792.  We are happy to see the Dentacoin Network growing steadily!  https://www.blog.dentacoin.com/first-clinic-taiwan-accepts-dentacoin-mr-iteeth-taipei-city/

Author: simplyaphilomath
Title: [ANN] Dentacoin [DCN] - The Blockchain Solution For The Global Dental Industry
Body: Hello guys! I am Tihomir Petrov from the Dentacoin team and I wanted to shed some light on your question. Our Co-Founder, Jeremias actually had already answered this question on Slack but as I see it has not been sent here.  "Hello @dinesh thanks for your feedback. If you check the address: https://etherscan.io/address/0xd560be7e053f6bdb113c2814faa339e29f4a385f you’ll see a total Dentacoin balance of about 148 billion Dentacoins so that’s not trillions or more. The reason that it shows that high number down in the transaction list is a bug in communication between Etherscan and our smart contract. It adds all the decimals and shows a huge amount. This is only a visual bug that does not change the balance of the account! So it doesn’t add any value or change it. To proof that just check the balance of the account"  TL;DR It was simply from the SmartContract which we will fix with the next update and we are sorry for this situation.

Title: [ANN] Dentacoin [DCN] - The Blockchain Solution For The Global Dental Industry
Body: As a investor (I invest 1 ETH for now), I have a question. How will you distribute the 1.9% on 2018? I'm quite confuse with the distribution because there's the possibility of price decrease if you directly add it in the blockchain without a price on it.  Based on the https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/dentacoin/, the circulating supply is 323,507,001,026.00 and the market cap is $41,899,333.00. If we divide the two:  $41,899,333 / 323,507,001,026.00 = $0.0001300 - This would be our Dollar price as of today November 16, 2017.  If you add 1.90% in 2018 that is:   8,000,000,000,000.00 x .019 =  152,000,000,000.00  So the total circulating supply in 2018 will be:  323,507,001,026.00 + 152,000,000,000.00 =  475,507,001,026.00  And we will get the value of 1 DCN in Dollar based on the current market cap:  $41,899,333 / 475,507,001,026.00 =  0.0000881  So, from 0.0001300$, the value on 2018 will become 0.0000881$ if the market cap will not increase. Hope you will get my point sir. I'm sure This will not be application of your token.

Author: dual77
Title: [ANN] Dentacoin [DCN] - The Blockchain Solution For The Global Dental Industry
Body: Now,  Message from the DCN crew :  Hello everyone! 😊 I can understand the frustration if you have expected results overnight. Thank you for your feedback!  However, let me emphasize again that Dentacoin, unlike most of the other projects, is all about its implementation into the real world. That's what would give it value. Speculations are nice short-term value triggers and I am not underestimating them, but the viable real value of a company/ a coin like ours is mainly built around the number of its users. On that note, these "few places" that have already implemented Dentacoin are essentially important first steps in that direction. At the moment our industry acquisition team is actively communicating with a big part of the dentists registered on our review platform who are willing to test our next tools and implement DCN into their workflow. More partners will come very soon  What you can and should expect from our team is hard work towards achieving the next targets on our Roadmap. As per this moment, we are even ahead of the plans described in the whitepaper, we are highly focused on attracting new participants into the Dentacoin network, we are working on the development and the constant upgrade of our tools, we are creating strategy to gain wider global awareness step by step and we are happy for the engagement and involvement of some of you in this process. The Assurance model, which a lot of you have already rightly recognized as a crucial part of our project, is being discussed and clarified at the moment as well.  Seeing the interest from the industry and people all over the world towards Dentacoin, I personally am convinced in its adoption and success. Yes, it might take time, it might be difficult sometimes, but the most important thing is to make steps. Every day. In the right direction.  I would like to come to my favorite topic "community" again... Your involvement always matters. You have an idea how to accelerate the good results? Share it. You have constructive critics against something we've done? Say it. But even better: Suggest what we could do to improve it. You want to see Dentacoin listed on a major exchange platform? Let this platform know about it. You want to be able to pay with DCN at your city? Let your dentist know about it. There is a meetup/a conference or any other event that you think could be of benefit for us to participate? Tell us about it. You would like to contribute in any way? We will be glad to cooperate with you.  At the end of the day, we all want this project to be successful, so we might as well make it possible together!

Author: dual77
Title: [ANN] Dentacoin [DCN] - The Blockchain Solution For The Global Dental Industry
Body: Dear Dentacoin supporters,  Soon after the successful initial token sale, we are happy to announce that the Dentacoin partner network is growing! A first clinic in India accepts Dentacoin as means of payment: Dentech Dental Care! "I believe that Dentacoin has the potential to improve the dental condition of the population on a global scale and to also strengthen the relationship between patients and dentists”, explains Dr. Yogesh Khadtare and adds: “In the long run dentists will get even more benefits from accepting DCN in their practice. The idea to shorten the supply chain by removing the dealer between dentists and manufacturers will make a revolution in the dental industry.”  Dentech Dental Care is the third clinic which has not only implemented the Dentacoin tools, but also accepts Dentacoin (DCN) as means of payment (after SWISS Dentaprime, Bulgaria and F3T Dental Clinic, United Kingdom).  Meanwhile, on our pilot tool - the Trusted Review Platform - there are already over 490 dental practices registered. A big part of them have expressed their interest in implementing Dentacoin at their practices and are eager to test the upcoming  Dentacare Mobile app with their patients. At the moment, our Industry Partner Acquisition team, headed by Dr. Klaus-Christian Werner, is actively communicating with them in order to establish cooperation.  https://www.dentacoin.com/blog/dentacoin-expands-accepted-means-payment-india/

Title: [ANN] Dentacoin [DCN] - The Blockchain Solution For The Global Dental Industry
Body: Hey thanks for doing your research and giving your opinion. As you said, the coins will be released gradually until the year 2042. Nobody knows what the future holds, but for now, we see that there is an increasing interest for Dentacoin concept - the first tool already has 4000+ registered users and 400+ dental clinics. The next 2 tools are on a test phase, so as soon as they are launched the awareness will increase even further. Many dental clinics and companies from the dental industry have expressed interest to integrate Dentacoin into their workflow. Once the ICO is over, the team will work towards these activities more. For the few months since being launched, Dentacoin has gained pretty good popularity and demand. Author: Nirmalpandey
Title: [ANN] Dentacoin [DCN] - The Blockchain Solution For The Global Dental Industry
Body: Dentacoin Foundation has launched the pilot of its blockchain-based Trusted Reviews Platform for users of dental services globally. In return for leaving detailed reviews of their actual dental treatment, patients are rewarded with Dentacoin (DCN), the custom token being sold as part of a current ICO and which is already accepted as payment by dental clinics across Europe.  $440 billion spent on dental treatments globally, but up to 90% of these expenses could be avoided if patients had early check-ups three times a year. By launching the review platform and linking it to DCN, Dentacoin Foundation hopes to leverage the network effect and increase the value of tokens for all participants. “With this latest update, we hope to make it very easy for people to contribute with reviews and trusted feedback about their dental treatment experiences”, says Jeremias Grenzebach, co-founder and core developer of Dentacoin alongside Alexander Atanasov, Trusted Review Platform developer.  Dentacoin already counts over 290 practices and over 2,400 registered users on the platform since it launched on 17th August. It hopes that the combined payment and reviews solution will create a more functional dental care system. Funds raised through the ICO will be used for focused regional targeting, with the aim of global coverage.  By encouraging direct feedback to dentists and clinics, the platform should lead to improved service quality. All DCN bought by users and issued as rewards by Dentacoin are held in an integrated blockchain wallet.  https://www.dataiq.co.uk/news/dentacoin-launches-blockchain-enabled-dental-reviews

Author: Nirmalpandey
Title: [ANN] Dentacoin [DCN] - The Blockchain Solution For The Global Dental Industry
Body: The Blockchain startup Dentacoin announced another key partnership with a German-based manufacturer  Nowadays, it is an undeniable fact that the Impact of the Blockchain technology goes far beyond financial services. As startups in different sectors use blockchain to drive greater transparency, veracity and automation across the digital information ecosystem, they’re boosting awareness of the technology in sectors ranging from payments to dentistry. Yes, you read it right. It is looking as though the Global Dental Industry is set for the greatest makeover within the Healthcare sector thanks to the Netherlands-based startup Dentacoin. Its custom-made token of the same name is already implemented at partner clinics, exchangeable on international exchange platforms, distributed through the first developed tools and since recently – accepted  as means of payment by a German-based manufacturer of high-tech dental equipment. But let’s first go back to the basics…  Using the Blockchain technology to start a global movement  Dentacoin is the first integral Blockchain solution for the Global Dentistry, aimed at improving dental care worldwide and making it affordable through creating a network of patients, dentists, suppliers, who trustfully cooperate between each other and act in mutual interest. The essence of this unusual Blockchain-based model lies in activating the decentralized power of all market participants through a custom-made utility token that serves numerous tailored Blockchain-based tools and powers the whole Dentacoin network. Within the network, network effects are expected where the value of the whole network increases with every new participant added to it. The token itself is used for rewarding network participants for their contribution to the Foundation’s mission; it is utilized as united means of payment and ensures access to services provided within and across the network. “The Blockchain technology is the only way to automate data security, protect from counterfeit and achieve low costs. It is the only way to integrate a currency system at low costs and with maximum security, independent of authorities and banks. The technology enables more and more decentralized, autonomous processes that return the power back into the hands of the people”, explains Jeremias Grenzebach, Co-Founder and Core-Developer at Dentacoin.  Already implemented as means of payment at partner clinics  If you are not aware of the current state of dentistry and its utter need of industry-centric solution or you are generally skeptical about the wide Blockchain acceptance, you might ask yourself if Dentacoin would be applicable into the real world anytime soon. You will not need to wonder for a long time though as Dentacoin has already been implemented as means of payment and as a part of their Patient Loyalty Programs at two partner clinics in Europe for months – SWISS Dentaprime (Varna, Bulgaria) and F3T Dental Clinic (London, United Kingdom). Therefore, even prior its ICO, Dentacoin already had its proof of concept.  Desislava Dimova, Manager of SWISS Dentaprime, the first clinic to implement DCN back in March 2017, shares more about their experience: “We are convinced that every business could and should benefit from collective customer wisdom in order to improve their service quality. […] Patients were also very excited about this new opportunity. Giving a discount in euro was nowhere near the excitement of receiving Dentacoin. Dentacoin felt like some kind of magical money to them. […] This creates a special bond between our clinic and the patients – all parties working together to improve the quality of dental services.”  Another key partnership with the German-based manufacturer CruisAIDer  Recently, the team behind this ambitious project made a significant breakthrough towards wider acceptance of Dentacoin within the industry. As of 9th of October 2017 CruisAIDer, a European company, specialized on digitalization of dental clinics in Germany, Austria and Switzerland, accepts Dentacoin as means of payment for its innovative product Powercart – a powerful machine that does everything the dentist needs to facilitate digital workflow and chairside treatment in a much faster and more efficient manner. Powercart is already being widely applied for intraoral scanning and compatible with the world’s leading brands for intraoral scanners.  “The dental industry is highly decentralized when it comes to parts and materials – we rely heavily on effective transfer of funds to increase productivity and live up to the fast-paced demands of our clients. Up until now we were stuck having to change between currencies to source the materials we need to manufacture our CruisAIDer Powercart for Intra-Oral scanning. In my opinion, Dentacoin is not only the future of the entire dental industry; it is what lies ahead for all connected supplementary industries. I wish we had this tool handy when we started out. Making the international acquisition of parts more efficient means we can cut prices”, says Simon Sostmann, CEO of CruisAIDer.  “Having a partnership with yet another European company, which strongly believes in digitalization and efficiency only proves the strong potential and opportunities which lay ahead of Dentacoin”, comments Philipp Grenzebach, Co-Founder and Business Developer at Dentacoin Foundation.  Currently, Dentacoin is raising funds for the further development of the project through an Initial Coin Offering which will be open until 1st of November 2017. The ICO is also a chance for early supporters to contribute at the lowest possible price (2 500 000 DCN/ETH, 33 000 000 DCN/BTC). The main modes of payment accepted during the ICO are Ether (ETH), Bitcoin (BTC) and Indian Rupee (INR). More information on how to participate in the ICO here: https://www.dentacoin.com/ico /  Thanks

Author: Nirmalpandey
Title: [ANN] Dentacoin [DCN] - The Blockchain Solution For The Global Dental Industry
Body: Bitcoin Denominations Define Supply  The use of the national currency can be one of the most confusing things about visiting a foreign land. Coins and bills have different values relative to each other. Although the math may be easy to grasp, the practical application of using the physical currency can create problems for the non-native. This same problem actually also exists in the world of cryptocurrencies.  Satoshi are Bitcoin Denomination  Of course, denominations of a national currency are necessary because cash is physically carried around and used in commerce. Bitcoin can also be divided into smaller units to accommodate any size transactions by simple math done automatically and invisibly by the transaction software. A portion of a Bitcoin can be split off to pay for something that costs far less than one Bitcoin, making denominations unnecessary.  This seamless splitting of a cryptocurrency into smaller units has a limit. For Bitcoin, the limit is 100,000,000. The term for each of these infinitesimally small units is a Satoshi. This means that one Bitcoin is actually worth one hundred million Satoshi. In the rapidly changing world of cryptocurrency the term “satoshi” may come to mean the smallest unit of any cryptocurrency, but for now it is limited to the smallest unit of Bitcoin.  When it took 10,000 Bitcoin to buy two pizzas worth $41 in 2010 the idea of Satoshi was nothing more than a programming feature, but as the value of Bitcoin increases Satoshi will begin to become useful denominations. In fact, the lexicon of Bitcoin includes units of Satoshi! One million Satoshi is called a Bitcent. This goes all the way down to one hundred Satoshi which is a “Youbit”.  Satoshi Defines Supply  There has already been some discussion in the Bitcoin community of reducing the standard unit of this cryptocurrency from the Bitcoin to one of these smaller units. While irrelevant from a mathematical perspective, this would have a positive psychological and practical value. Smaller units of Bitcoin would be understood more easily relative to what they can buy, which may increase the value.  This is an absolutely fascinating progression in the perceived value of cryptocurrencies as a deflationary hedge, but the practical application is more meaningful. As of October, 2017 there are 16.6 million Bitcoin in circulation. In fact, this number is misleading. Because each Bitcoin can be divided into 100,000,00 parts, the actual number of units of the Bitcoin cryptocurrency in circulation is 1.66 quadrillion!  Moving decimal places around by breaking one Bitcoin into its component parts is not an academic exercise. Currencies have denominations for a variety of reasons, and only some of them are practical. The psychological impact on the market value of Bitcoin could be significant if people realized the large number of units actually currently on the market.  Satoshi vs. Dentacoin  This fact is demonstrated by the concerns about the number of Dentacoin that have been pre-mined. 8 trillion tokens seems to be enough to permanently reduce the value of each token to an infinitely small value, but this concern ignores the fact that Bitcoin has achieved significant value with over 200 times this number of units in circulation.  There are two important points to be made here. The first is that Dentacoin is not divisible into any smaller unit. For Dentacoin, one Dentacoin equals one “satoshi”. So the comparison between one Dentacoin and one Bitcoin is inaccurate. The real comparison is between one Dentacoin and one Satoshi. This is parity and the honest basis for any comparison of the two currencies.  Secondly, not all of the 8 trillion Dentacoin will be released onto the market at one time. The total supply is designed to facilitate the use of Dentacoin as a global unit of currency in the dental market. Dentacoin will be released on a pre-determined, set schedule that will increase the supply as the demand and awareness for the coin grows. This is intended to provide a firm foundation for Dentacoin from which it can increase in value.  Understanding the actual underlying unit of a currency, either national or crypto, is key to appreciating both its utility and its true value. And the fact is that it is easy to get lost in the math of decimal places. But doing this with both Dentacoin and Bitcoin is absolutely critical in order to grasp how Dentacoin has the ability to increase in value as it is accepted as the key to better global dental health.  https://www.dentacoin.com/blog/total-supply-bitcoin-200-times-token-supply-dentacoin/

And while some companies are still focused solely on its application to handle payments, others are about to change a whole industry by activating the decentralized power of the crowd through a custom-made token. Meet Dentacoin – the first integral Blockchain Solution for the global dental industry, aimed at improving dental care worldwide and making it affordable. Through the development and implementation of numerous value-generating Blockchain-based tools, the introduction of two innovative dental clinic concepts and the creation of a custom Ethereum token that serves as the chain and the base layer for all the tools, Dentacoin maps out the road to a revolution of the entire dental industry...more

Author: cryptohero2017
Title: [ANN] Dentacoin [DCN] - The Blockchain Solution For The Global Dental Industry
Body: Hey guys. Yes, 8 trillion is the total DCN supply and there are good reasons for that. 76% of all the coins are locked in contracts and will be released bit by bit from 2018 to 2042, following a certain schedule. Around 40% of the total amount of Dentacoins are reserved for EARNING (through tools and value-generating activities, contributing to the improvement of the dental industry), 40% are reserved for BUYING (ICO and presale activities, crowdfunding) and the other 20% are to be utilized by the Dentacoin Foundation for development of tools, marketing activities, bounty programs, future projects and unpredicted expenses.  See details here: https://www.dentacoin.com/blog/why-did-we-premine-8-trillion-dentacoins/  The planned allocation of the total DCN supply is described in the Whitepaper, chapter Allocation and supply: https://dentacoin.com/white-paper/Whitepaper-en.pdf  Actually, if you understand our distribution concept, you might even get concerned if there will be enough coins, as it happened with BitcoinChaser: http://bitcoinchaser.com/ico-hub/dentacoin-interview

Title: [ANN] Dentacoin [DCN] - The Blockchain Solution For The Global Dental Industry
Body: Hello and thanks for your feedback. The Concept of Dentacoin is Global. The minimum required volume of a currency in order to have a chance for a global use is 5% of the total FIAT currencies volume. Today, all of the world’s money equals USD 160 trillion. The total amount of Dentacoins produced is 8 trillion, meaning 1000 DCN/person when calculating with the estimated 8 billion future world populations. 8 trillion DCN is an equivalent to approximately 5% of the above mentioned USD 160 trillion. To say it simple: the total volume of Dentacoins produced covers the minimum requirement for a currency to be recognized as global.

Author: cryptohero2017
Title: [ANN] Dentacoin [DCN] - The Blockchain Solution For The Global Dental Industry
Body: Hello and thanks for getting in touch.  Amalgam is probably the most controversial filler in dentistry. Although it is easy to use, it involves immense health risks.  It can not be in the air because it is a mercury alloy. Mercury exists in liquid or solid form but can not be gaseous. However, if the mercury is open, it is possible to slowly form fumes even at room temperature, which can cause poisoning. Mercury itself is highly toxic, harmful to health and the environment.  For this reason, not only the use in humans, but also the disposal of the material is dangerous. Both of these factors have led to amalgam being discouraged and a general ban is now being considered. Whether this will be the case will be the pending test.

Author: cryptohero2017
Title: [ANN] Dentacoin [DCN] - The Blockchain Solution For The Global Dental Industry
Body: Dentacoin is the first Blockchain solution created for the global dental industry. This one-of-a-kind business model uses the current state of the existing industry and introduces solutions to specific problems. The mission of Dentacoin is to improve dental care and make it accessible for everyone worldwide.   Dentacoin is developing a number of blockchain-based tools, as well as introducing two innovative dental clinic concepts, technologically advanced and highly efficient, developed as future business models for the global dental industry. Among the tools of Dentacoin are a Trusted Review Platform (already up-and-running), Dentacare Mobile App, DentaVox webapp, Dentacoin Assurance, a Trading Platform for dental care products, materials and equipment and a Database for medical records. All tools have blockchain integrated functionalities and are served by a custom ERC20 token, also named Dentacoin.  *** Dentacoin was introduced in February 2017 and for the short time until now: -   Distributed over 303 billion coins; -   Maintains rank in the top 100 cryptocurrencies on Coinmarketcap; -   Bought a company, entirely paid for with DCN; -   Reported success in a newly-developed “proof-of-concept” dental clinic with Blockchain integrated functionalities; -   Developed and launched its pilot tool - Dentacoin Trusted Review Platform (with more than 1900 users and 200 dental practices registered); -   Was implemented as means of payment at partner dental clinics in Europe; -   Was accepted as means of payment by high-tech dental equipment manufacturer; -   Was listed for trading on several international exchange platform; -   Gathered a community of over 40 000 people globally, waiting for the upcoming ICO.   Distribution mechanism: https://www.dentacoin.com/blog/crazy-enough-to-premine-8-trillion-dentacoins/  Official website: www.dentacoin.com  Twitter: twitter.com/dentacoin  Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/dentacoin/  Whitepaper: https://www.dentacoin.com/white-paper/Whitepaper-en1.pdf  RoadMap:    Dentacoin is an industrial blockchain concept invented by Dentacoin Foundation in the Netherlands. The Dentacoin ERC20 token  ( https://github.com/dentacoin/Dentacoin ) is configured to be used globally by all individuals.  Team: Since 2014, approximately 120 people have been involved in different aspects of the concept development.  Prof. Dr. Dimitar Dimitrakiev Founder of Dentacoin Foundation The Founder. Highly respected University lecturer. More than 27 years experience in financial markets. Devoted to science and engineering. Member of the IEEE Computational Intelligence society, EADM and Union of Automation and Informatics.  Jeremias Grenzebach Co-Founder / Core Developer Our Code Wizard. Early entrant into the Blockchain scene. Immersed within the peer-to-peer technology for 8 years. Contributor to Ethereum, Waves, ZCash, uPort, Status, imToken, Byteball. Strong believer in decentralization and transparency.  Philipp Grenzebach Co-Founder / Business Developer / M&A The Economic Brain behind Dentacoin. Studies in Law, Economics and Business Management. Adopted the tripple bottom line to Dentacoin while integrating technical sustainability. Fighter for free, decentralised markets.  Veselin Matov CRM & Supply Chain Manager Our CRM Pro. Focused on identifying technological trends and implementing them as competitive advantages. Experienced in CRM, Dental Software Implementation, Purchasing Management. Background education in Computer Systems and Technology. Constantly exploring state-of-the-art innovations for the benefit of patients.  Hristo Gradechliev CFO The Finance Master. Responsible for managing the finance and accounting divisions. MBA in Law. Experienced in payment ecosystems, building analytic tools, processes and teams to manage the revenue, costs and risks inherent in the payment space. With a strong flair for successful investments.  Julia Radeva Business Development Manager Our Business Pioneer. 11-year experience in Business Development Management. The driving force behind several successful dental clinic concepts. Overseeing the applications of dental innovations and constantly exploring the opportunities for growth in Dental Industry.  Tsvetomir Ivanov Industry 4.0 Engineer The Future Thinker. Digital Dentistry, CAD/CAM and 3D-printing expert. Highly focused on finding ways to achieve significant efficiency, cost reduction and revenue gains through digitalization and automation. Permanently researching, evaluating and implementing high-tech dental innovations.  Sergey Ushakov Digital Transformation Specialist Our Transformation Accelerator. Computer science and Blockchain enthusiast. Degree in Robotics & Mechatronics; currently specializing in Software Engineering. Experienced in Digital Transformations and Business Process Automation. Highly interested in AI, IoT, VR and AR.  Dr. Dimo Daskalov Dental Industry Development Catalyst The Strongest Link between DCN and the Dental Industry. Leading dentist, currently managing a team of 19 dentists. Educator in Prosthetic Dentistry. Constantly improving dental services by implementing future technologies, delivering “WOW” patient experience and simultaneously reducing the costs. Eager to be a part of the paradigm shift.  Dr. Ivan Peev Dentistry 4.0 Specialist Our Guide to the Digital Implantology world. Dental Implant Specialist with a significant experience in providinghigh-tech dental care by surgical guides and computer-navigated implantation systems. Phantom instructor, certified by the International Training Center for Dental Implantology (IFZI). With a Sixth sense for cutting-edge technical solutions.  Betina Bogdanova Senior Legal Advisor The Voice of law. Supports the legal project management pillar of Dentacoin. Experienced in advising fintech and dental companies. Solid legal background including the Australian National University, Rijks Univesitet and Harvard Law. Previous collaborations with the WHO and Harvard School of Public Health.  Donika Kraeva Strategic Communications Manager The Communications Ambassador. Translates big and complex ideas to the target group's language. Experienced in Online Medical Marketing. Developed Feedback Systems and Patient Loyalty Programs for international dental clinics. Seeking ways to utilize Blockchain advantages in building a patient-driven Dental Industry.  Mariam Nishanian Online Reputation & Public Relations Our Public Voice. International background in PR, social media management, communications consulting and UX design. Skilled entrepreneur with experience in start-up development. In constant pursuit of new challenges.  Ayredin Stoyanov Graphic Designer Our Visual Power. Education in Multimedia Design and Software Systems and Technologies. Experienced in using visuals to communicate ideas that inspire, inform and captivate. Passionate about video creation and photography.
